Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop @baby potatoes{500%grams} into 2cm chunks. Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed). Slice into 1cm rounds.

Pick the @rosemary{1%unit} leaves.

Trim the @parsnip{1%unit} and halve lengthways. Cut into 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop potato, parsnip and carrot on a lined #baking tray{}. Toss with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste}, rosemary and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. Roast on top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

Zest and halve the @lemon{1%unit}. Juice one half and cut the other half into thick wedges.

Lay the @Irish chicken breast{320%grams} out on a #board{} and place a hand flat on top. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Place a large #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}. When hot, add the chicken steaks and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Cook through, ~{3-6%minutes} each side. IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Once cooked, remove from the pan and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Cook in batches if the pan is too crowded.

Return the pan to medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste} if necessary. Once hot, fry the onion until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add @honey{sachet{1}}, @mustard{sachet{1}}, @chicken stock{sachet{1}}, @sugar{1%tbsp} (per 2P) and @water{50%ml} (per 2P) to the pan.

Stir in lemon zest and @lemon juice{1%tbsp}. If you want things more tart add more lemon juice, tasting as you go.

Cook, stirring, until the sauce thickens slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the chicken back to the pan and cook, ensuring to coat well in the sauce. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the sauce if necessary.

Divide the @baby spinach{60%grams} and roast veg between plates. Top with the chicken.

Drizzle over the lemony sauce from the pan. Serve the lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.